Time for us to get started. So I'm Paul Michiel.

3
00:00:07.980 --> 00:00:11.630
I've had the privilege this year of being the program chair

4
00:00:12.360 --> 00:00:14.920
for this annual meeting and to do that with Dr.

5
00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:18.880
Alice Shaw and to work with a marvelous AACR

6
00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:20.820
team in putting together this program.

7
00:00:21.800 --> 00:00:25.780
This session that we're talking about today is on extrachromosomal DNA,

8
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:29.300
and I want to draw a few parallels, if I might.

9
00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:33.680
So I'm going to give an opening talk to set the table

10
00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:37.360
to the field and what's happening with regard to biological

11
00:00:37.460 --> 00:00:40.520
insight and where it's going. We're then going to hear

12
00:00:40.660 --> 00:00:44.449
from the HDSI Chancellor's

13
00:00:44.540 --> 00:00:45.120
Professor,

14
00:00:46.060 --> 00:00:49.630
Dr. Vineet Bafna from UCSD, who's going to be talking about

15
00:00:49.700 --> 00:00:53.200
tools and how we capacitate research across the field.

16
00:00:53.530 --> 00:00:56.760
And then we're going to hear from Professor Mahim Jamal Hanjani, who's been a true

17
00:00:56.920 --> 00:01:00.440
pioneer as a lung oncologist who goes all the way from

18
00:01:00.480 --> 00:01:04.121
mechanism to studying patients. And the topic is all going to be around

19
00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:08.400
extrachromosomal DNA. There's a tagline for this

20
00:01:08.440 --> 00:01:11.380
year's meeting that has to do with

21
00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:14.480
precision about the science of medicine.

22
00:01:14.740 --> 00:01:18.690
Purpose, to have our science go all the way to saving patients'

23
