00:42:34.436 --> 00:42:37.116
The problem is actually surprisingly hard.

717
00:42:37.916 --> 00:42:40.856
And this picture hopefully can illustrate some of that.

718
00:42:40.916 --> 00:42:44.796
So here on the left is an amplicon graph that amplicon architect

719
00:42:44.856 --> 00:42:48.776
or any sort of genomic analysis tool can create.

720
00:42:49.236 --> 00:42:52.836
If you want to know what's on the ecDNA, we sort of know that it's these

721
00:42:52.936 --> 00:42:56.928
segments A, B, C, and D.But we don't quite know in which order, in

